{{Infobox military conflict |conflict=Action of 1595 |partof= |image= |caption= |date=June or July 1595 |place=off [[Longina]] |result=Indecisive |combatant1={{flagicon|SMOM}} [[History of Malta under the Order of Saint John|Order of Saint John]] |combatant2={{flag|Ottoman Empire|1453}} |commander1= |commander2= |strength1= 5 [[galleys]] |strength2= 3 galleys |casualties1= |casualties2= }}
The '''Action of 1595''' was an indecisive [[navy|naval]] battle between forces of [[Malta]], then [[History of Malta under the Order of Saint John|under the protection]] of the [[Knights Hospitaller|Order of Saint John]], and [[Bizerte]], then part of the [[Ottoman Empire]].
The [[battle]] took place in late June or early July 1595, after five [[Malta|Maltese]] [[galley]]s sailed south from [[Syracuse, Italy|Syracuse]] and encountered three [[Bizerte|Bizertine]] galleys off [[Longina]]. Two Maltese galleys failed to engage and the Bizertines escaped. There was some damage on both sides.
==Ships involved==
===Malta=== * ''Capitana'' * ''San Fede'' * ''San Croce'' * ''Vittoria'' * ''San Placido''
===Bizerte=== 3 galleys
