The '''Zhukov Air and Space Defense Academy''' is a [[Russia]]n [[military academy]] located on the banks of the [[Volga River]] in Kalinin (now [[Tver]]). The academy, formed in 1956, is named after [[Georgy Zhukov|Soviet Marshal G.K. Zhukov]]. It is one of the main education centers of the [[Russian Aerospace Defence Forces|Aerospace Defense Force]].
[[File:Tver military academy.jpg|240px|thumb|left]]

In addition to its educational and training mandate, this academy is a research center for studying problems of operational art and tactics, as well as command, communications, and control (C3) on air defense matters. 

