''' Aribinda Airport ''' {{airport codes|XAR|DFOY}} is an [[airport]] serving the village of [[Aribinda]] in the [[Soum Province]], part of the [[Sahel Region]] of [[Burkina Faso]].
Airport is likely long abandoned. There is currently no paved or marked runway near any of six different coordinate pairs for Aribinda available on the internet. Neither is any historical or runway information posted at any web site with a page for Aribinda.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.21700,-0.88300,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.23333,-0.86667,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.217000,-0.883000,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.215278,-0.895555,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.21694,-0.88306,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/@14.21667,-0.88306,2000m/data=!3m1!1e3|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|language=en|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref> However, a listing for the airfield still appears in the official ASECNA Aeronatical Information Publication for Burkina Faso, quoting coordinates N14 13.0 W000 53.0.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ais-asecna.org/en/ad/ad2.htm|title=AIS ASECNA - Ad.2 : Aérodromes|website=www.ais-asecna.org|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref> Furthermore, the airport still has a valid 3-letter code allocated by IATA,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iata.org/publications/Pages/code-search.aspx|title=IATA - Codes - Airline and Airport Codes Search|last=IATA|website=www.iata.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref> though a search of the ICAO database reveals no 4-letter ICAO location indicator code.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.icao.int/safet