{{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Spain}} "Ella no es ella" | image = | caption = | year = 1994 | country = Spain | artist = [[Alejandro Abad]] | as = | with = | language = Spanish | languages = | composer = Alejandro Abad | lyricist = Alejandro Abad | conductor = Josef Llobell | place = 18th | points = 17 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?info.1994es from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Hombres | prev_link = Hombres (song) | next = Vuelve conmigo | next_link = Vuelve conmigo }}
"'''Ella no es ella'''" ({{IPA-es|ˈeʎa no ˈes ˈeʎa}}, "{{lang|en|She's Not Her}}") was the [[Spain|Spanish]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1994]], performed in [[Spanish language|Spanish]] by [[Alejandro Abad]]. The song was also written by Abad.
The song was performed 21st on the night, following [[Austria]]'s [[Petra Frey]] with "[[Für den Frieden der Welt]]" and preceding [[Hungary]]'s [[Friderika Bayer]] with "[[Kinek mondjam el vétkeimet?]]".
At the close of voting, it had received 17 points, placing 18th in a field of 25.
It was succeeded as [[Spain in the Eurovision Song Contest|Spanish representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1995|1995 Contest]] by [[Anabel Conde]] singing "[[Vuelve conmigo]]".
