[[File:Heiðarvíga saga.jpg|thumb|240px|''Heiðarvíga saga'' from a copy of the University of Copenhagen.]]
'''''Heiðarvíga saga''''' ({{Audio|Is-Heiðarvígarsaga.oga|listen}}) or '''''The Story of the Heath-Slayings''''' is one of the [[Icelanders' sagas]]. It is badly preserved; 12 leaves of the only surviving manuscript were destroyed along with their only copy in the [[Copenhagen Fire of 1728|fire of Copenhagen]] in 1728. The content of that part is only known through a summary written from memory by [[Jón Grunnvíkingur]] who had made the lost copy.

The saga has been taken by some scholars as possibly among the oldest Icelanders' sagas.

