Two types of '''musical bow''' are common in [[Latvia]]:  the ''spēles'' and the ''pūšļa vijole''. The ''spēles'' is simply a primitive [[musical bow]] that can be plucked, or bowed with a second bow. While the ''pūšļa vijole'' ({{lang-en|bladder fiddle}}) adds an inflated animal bladder as a resonator.<ref>{{cite web |first=Amanda |last=Jātniece |title=A primer on Latvian folk instruments |url=http://latviansonline.com/a-primer-on-latvian-folk-instruments/ |accessdate=November 28, 2016 |website=Latvians Online |date=March 21, 2009}}</ref>

