Panj Peer (or Panj Pir), the Five Great Saints, mentioned in South Asian ([[Punjabi people|Punjabi]]) literature<ref>[http://www.wichaar.com/news/132/ARTICLE/4803/2008-05-07.html ਹੀਰ ਵਾਰਿਸ ਸ਼ਾਹ: ਬੰਦ 82 ਡਾਕਟਰ ਮਨਜ਼ੂਰ ਇਜਾਜ਼]</ref> are as follows:

* [[Data Ganj Baksh]](Al-Hajveri, of Lahore, Punjab) 
* [[Fariduddin Ganjshakar|Sheikh Baba Farid Shakarganj]] (Pakpattan, Punjab)
* [[Baha-ud-din Zakariya|Baha'ud din Zakariya]] (Multan, Punjab)
* [[Lal Shahbaz Qalandar]] (Sehwan, Sindh)
* [[Jalaluddin Surkh-Posh Bukhari|Sayyad Jalaluddin Bukhari 'Laal Shah']] also known as Makhdoom Jahaaniyaan (Ucch, Punjab).

These are mentioned in the great love-epic of the [[Sufi]] poet Sayyid [[Waris Shah]] "[[Heer Ranjha]]", which opens with an invocation to these holy sages.

