The '''Universidade Amílcar Cabral'''  (UAC) is a public institution of higher education in [[Bissau]], Guinea-Bissau. The only public university in the country, it was established in 2003 by President [[Henrique Pereira Rosa]], but in 2010 it underwent restructuring after becoming extinct in 2008, and became affiliated with the [[Universidade Lusófona da Guiné]] (ULG). In 2013, it resumed its activities with the appointment of its new governing body, and is it is run by the Ministry of Education. In May 2015, [[UNESCO]] reportedly donated about $600,000 worth of computer equipment to the university.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unmultimedia.org/radio/portuguese/2015/05/equipamento-novo-e-desafios-adicionais-para-universidade-amilcar-cabral/|title=Equipamento novo e desafios adicionais para Universidade Amílcar Cabral|publisher=Unmultimedia.org|date=19 May 2015|accessdate=29 May 2015|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

